title: OceaniaR Hackathon 2024
text:
We are excited to announce the first OceaniaR Hackathon day. This event is a chance to collaborate in-person on R-focused projects for social good, with some of the leading developers in the R community. There will also be time to hold informal talks to share ideas, concepts and new packages for feedback.
This event will have a focus on promoting projects and participation from R users in the Oceania region including Australia, New Zealand and the Pacific Islands.
All project ideas will be listed as Issues on the project Github and decided on the day.

title: OceaniaR Hackathon 2024
text:
Join Us
If you would like to attend. Please complete the following Expression of Interest.
There is no charge for the event.
We are excited to offer a diversity scholarship up to $1000 to support travel costs for persons who are from underrepresented groups to attend this day, in addition to participating in the 2024 WOMBAT meeting.






Note



Due to limited space, completing this form does not guarantee attendance. The organizers will strive to ensure a diverse mix of attendees and we regret that not all interested persons will be able to attend the event.

title: OceaniaR Hackathon 2024
text:
When
Monday 21st October 2024. 9:00am - 4:00pm. In-person only.
This is the day before the WOMBAT 2024 meeting in Melbourne on the 22nd & 23rd October. More info coming soon!
